FBIS3-30438 "dreeu023_d_94001" FBIS-EEU-94-023 Document Type:Daily Report 3 Feb 1994 SLOVAKIA Meciar Rejects Talks on Hungarian Rights LD0302125994 Budapest Kossuth Radio Network in Hungarian 0900 GMT 3 Feb 94 LD0302125994 Budapest Kossuth Radio Network Language: Hungarian Article Type:BFN [Text] The Slovak prime minister [Vladimir Meciar] said that he is not willing to hold talks on the Hungarian minority's collective rights, because the rights of the Hungarian minority in Slovakia, as he said, are already excessive. At a Bratislava rally of his party, the Movement for a Democratic Slovakia, Meciar said, we quote: There is complete freedom in Slovakia, therefore, those who want to leave can do so at any time. He added that the Slovak Government will not pursue a policy to suit certain circles of the Hungarian Republic.
